CNCP v1 23123
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#10814: A type for a vnode as the first argument of h() is missing",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:22:53.494802+00:00",
  "text": "A type for a vnode as the first argument of h() is missing\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.4.25\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://play.vuejs.org/#\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nUse `h` instead of `cloneVNode` without typescript\n\n### What is expected?\n\nSome warning about an invalid argument\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\n`h` works exactly as `cloneVNode` since it redirects arguments to `cloneVNode`\n\n### System Info\n\n_No response_\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\nSince a vnode is fully supported as the first argument, add a type for it and update the docs (another issue: https://github.com/vuejs/docs/issues/2834)",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: types"
  ],
  "embedding": {
    "model": "granite-embedding-278m-multilingual",
